      <span>
        After 11 days, 8 hours, and 15 minutes from Savannah, Michael J Coles achieved a new world 
        record. Sleeping just 22 hours total, less than two hours each day, he shattered his record at 
                        40, lifting his bike on destination courthouse steps, -nothing would ever be the same.
      </span>
    </p>
